	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs5E1DB61D">WEST virginia legislature</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 regular session</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Committee Substitute</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">for</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 4002</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Dittman, Chiarelli, Willis, Statler, Stephens, Amos, J. Cannon, Ellington, Canterbury, Ferrell, and Parsons</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Originating in the Committee on Education; Reported on January 20, 2026]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding a new article, designated &sect;4-16-1, &sect;4-16-2, and &sect;4-16-3, relating to establishing the West Virginia Collaboratory; establishing powers and duties; directing funding; establishing an advisory group; specifying composition and duties of the advisory group; authorizing reimbursement of members; exempting meetings of the advisory group from open meetings laws; exempting documents compiled by the advisory group from public records requests; and requiring annual reports.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs456817A0">ARTICLE 16. THE WEST VIRGINIA COLLABORATORY.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;4-16-1. The West Virginia Collaboratory established.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&nbsp;(a) There is established the West Virginia Collaboratory (Collaboratory) to facilitate the dissemination of the policy and research expertise of state institutions of higher education within West Virginia, as that term is defined in &sect;18B-1-2 of this code, for practical use by state and local governments and for the benefit of the citizens of the State of West Virginia. The Collaboratory shall be housed at Marshall University. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The Collaboratory shall do at least the following within the funds available by appropriation of the Legislature:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Conduct, manage, or participate in research projects and opportunities that may be of interest to citizens and policymakers within the state, </span><a name="_Hlk219802362"><span class="cs46AE26E6">including, but not limited to, research in the areas of workforce development, public education, economic development, and natural resources management, including, but not limited to, research related to the environmental and economic components of the management of the natural resources within the state and of new technologies for habitat, environmental, and water quality improvements</span></a><span class="cs46AE26E6">;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Support research programs at institutions of higher education within the Collaboratory&rsquo;s areas of focus and expertise;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Identify, pursue, and support research and development opportunities through technology research and development, including, but not limited to, funding opportunities and partnerships between institutions of higher education, government agencies, nonprofit organizations, and both private and public businesses;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Develop and disseminate relevant best practices to interested parties; lead or participate in projects across the state; and make policy, research, funding, and other recommendations to the Legislature;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) Assist the Office of State Fire Marshal in the maintenance of standard safe practices for the discharge of Aqueous Film-Forming Foams (AFFF) as may be established by legislative rule under the authority of &sect;29-3-5g of this code; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(6) Teach and train students and faculty to engage in and administer neutral and unbiased research and advice on science policy through:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(A) Informal workshops and similar events; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(B) Formal development and delivery of curriculum.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) The following applies to funding received by the Collaboratory:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Funds appropriated by the Legislature and used by the Collaboratory may not be used for indirect overhead costs at a state institution of higher education partnering with the Collaboratory.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) All units of state and local government shall cooperate with and assist in any research program of the Collaboratory which shall include at least the following:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(A) Access to infrastructure;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(B) Access to personnel; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(C) The sharing of information and data necessary or helpful to the accomplishment of the duties of the Collaboratory free of charge, subject to the provisions of applicable state and federal law.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) The Collaboratory may expend such moneys as are necessary to enter into cooperative agreements with non-academic entities partnering with a state institution of higher education in furtherance of completing research projects in accordance with the provisions of this article.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) The Collaboratory may allocate funds for capital improvements on or in any property owned or operated by Marshall University to carry out research and development projects in which the Collaboratory has funded completely or in part.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) The Collaboratory may negotiate or impose data use, data management, and revenue sharing requirements for intellectual property developed through its research awards using state funds, including, but not limited to, contractual terms that provide for gross revenue distribution to the general fund.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(6) Funds appropriated by the Legislature to the Collaboratory shall not revert to the general revenue of the state but shall remain available until expended. </span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;4-16-2. Advisory group.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) There is hereby established the Collaboratory Advisory Group, which shall consist of the following members:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Two members of the House of Delegates, to be appointed by the Speaker of the House of Delegates;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Two members of the Senate, to be appointed by the President of the Senate;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) A designee of Marshall University, to be appointed by the President of Marshall University;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) A designee of West Virginia University, to be appointed by the President of West Virginia University;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) A designee of West Virginia State University, to be appointed by the President of West Virginia State University;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(6) The Chancellor of the Higher Education Policy Commission, or his or her designee; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(7) Two persons who are citizens and residents of the state, to be appointed by agreement of the Speaker of the House of Delegates and the President of the Senate, who possess a broad understanding of the relationship between public and private sector research.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The Collaboratory Advisory Group shall assist the Collaboratory in establishing priorities and developing protocols for purposes of identifying research opportunities contemplated by this article and may:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Recommend timely research and project ideas to the Collaboratory to fund as well as anticipate and identify emerging topics and relevant policy issues for future projects;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Help identify higher education subject matter experts to lead and contribute to Collaboratory projects;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Utilize their expertise and experience to define the work of the Collaboratory&rsquo;s research projects and prioritize research projects;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Review and recommend modifications to funding proposals and projects under consideration by the Collaboratory; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) Review and recommend modifications to all Collaboratory reports and publications ensuring accuracy and objectivity.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) The Collaboratory Advisory Group members shall be reimbursed from funds of the Collaboratory for sums necessary to carry out its responsibilities and for reasonable travel expenses to attend meetings.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) Meetings of the Collaboratory Advisory Group are not subject to the provisions of &sect;6-9A-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. of this code. Any records compiled by the Collaboratory Advisory Group in furtherance of its duties are not public records and are not subject to disclosure in response to a Freedom of Information Act request under &sect;29B-1-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. of this code.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;4-16-3. Annual report.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">By December 1 of each year, the Collaboratory shall report to the Joint Committee on Government and Finance </span><a name="_Hlk219795400"><span class="cs46AE26E6">on its activities in the prior fiscal year and any legislative recommendations. The report shall include a summary of the administration of accounts and expenditures from appropriated funds. </span></a></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p>


